Description: The European Patent Office (EPO) provides access to millions of patent documents. It provides those data in a standardized XML format. Datasets for the last six weeks can be obtained for free through the data portal of the EPO. Older documents need to be obtained via DVD on a paid basis. If you want to browse the data- please use the links in the "navigation box" on the left side. Furthermore- it is possible to create your own SPARQL queries for obtaining lists of combined information. This dataset (http://epo.publicdata.eu/) was triplified and published by the research group AKSW (Agile Knowledge Engineering and Semantic Web). For further information about AKSW please visit our website.
